{
  "texts": [
    "This confirms the hypothesis that digital food environments structurally discourage healthy food choices.",
    "Youngsters make choices subjectively or based on presumed taste value rather than established nutritional facts in most cases, simply due to the lack of clear-cut guidelines on electronic menus.",
    "Thus, nutrition becomes secondary.",
    "This is backed up by the Theory of Planned Behavior, which shows intention exists, but perceived control and environmental cues limit behavior change.",
    "Many respondents thus act in a reverse way to their health intentions."
  ]
}